This paper involves the implementation of a case-based reasoning approach to mediation, which involves the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of analogical and commonsense reasoning components, which are related to the fields of machine learning and natural language processing, respectively. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of ontologies, which are related to the field of cybernetics, and the analysis of conflicts, which is related to the field of cryptography. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the cs.CY (Cybernetics) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-categories.
